- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is likely because the paper deals with discrete optimization problems (p-median and p-center clustering) and proves their optimality.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely because the paper mentions the use of multi-objective meta-heuristics to archive diversified non-dominated points along the Pareto front.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is possible because clustering is a common technique in machine learning, but the paper does not explicitly mention any machine learning applications.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is possible because the paper analyzes the computational complexity of the proposed algorithms.
